This paper is about handwriting recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed methodology involves using a language model to refine predictions, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses transfer learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of unlabeled data and bootstrapping is a common technique in both unsupervised learning (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
